The paper deals with the complexity of a problem related to database queries, specifically Boolean queries with self-joins. This falls under the category of database systems and theory, which is covered by cs.DB. The paper also involves analyzing the structural properties of the queries, which could fall under computational complexity (cs.CC) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of reductions to network flow suggests a connection to optimization and control theory (cs.LO), while the overall problem of resilience in queries could potentially involve artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques.
